Cupcakes:200g unsalted butter, softened370g caster sugar5ml (1 tsp) vanilla paste4 eggs415g self-raising flour5ml (1 tsp) ground cinnamon250ml (1 cup) full-cream milk150g Pink Lady apples, grated and cubedCrumble:250g unsalted butter, softened250g brown sugar110g icing sugar270g almond flourIcing:250g Philadelphia cream cheese250g cr me fra che110g unsalted butter, softened270g icing sugarTo serve:Apple peel shavings, to garnishMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C. Line a muffin tray with cupcake cases.2) For the cupcakes, cream the butter, caster sugar and vanilla paste together with an electric mixer. Add the eggs one at a time, beating until just combined. Sift the flour and cinnamon together. Gradually fold in the flour and milk. Fold the grated and cubed apple into the mixture.3) Fill the cupcake cases with equal amounts of filling. Bake for 20+ minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean. Leave the cupcakes to cool in the tray for 5 minutes before removing.4) To make the crumble, turn down the oven to 160 C. Line a baking tray with baking paper. Place all the ingredients into a mixing bowl, and combine with a dough hook. Crumble pieces onto the baking tray. Bake in the oven until golden.5) For the icing, combine the cream cheese, cr me fra che and butter with a paddle attachment. Sift the icing sugar into the mixture, and mix until smooth. Transfer to a piping bag.6) To serve, pipe the icing onto the cupcakes. Sprinkle with crumble. Top with shavings of apple peel.